Most AI agent projects fail in production.
Not because the model was bad.
Not because the code was messy.
because the developer didn't understand the 4 parts  and skipped one of them
Here's what each part fixes, and what breaks when you ignore it.
 Perception — how it reads the world
Fixes: agent acting on assumptions instead of real data
Skip it → your agent is blind. It will act on stale prices, wrong balances, outdated state. Confidently. Every single time.
Memory — what it carries forward
Fixes: agent repeating the same mistake on every run
Skip it → your agent is a goldfish. It hits the same failed API on every cycle, burns gas for hours, and never learns that the strategy stopped working at 2am.
 Reasoning — how it decides what to do
Fixes: agent taking the first action it sees instead of the right one
Skip it → your agent is reckless. It grabs the first tool available and executes  no second check, no edge case handling, no fallback.
 Action —what it actually does
Fixes: agent reasoning perfectly but never executing
Skip it → your agent is useless. But more importantly if Action has no limits spending caps, access control, circuit breakers your perfectly reasoning agent will drain the wallet doing exactly what you told it to do.

What actually happens when builders skip these:
✗ Stale perception → agent doesn't liquidate → protocol takes the loss
✗ No memory → same failed call loops for hours → gas burns unnoticed  
✗ No reasoning depth → wrong transaction executed with confidence
✗ Unlimited action → agent reasons correctly → wallet drained anyway

What you get when all 4 are done right:
✓ Real-time on-chain data  no assumptions, no stale reads
✓ Agent that learns from its own past runs  sharper every cycle
✓ Step-by-step reasoning before committing to any action
✓ Execution bounded by on-chain rules  powerful but controlled

The uncomfortable truth:
Most "AI agent" projects are just LLM wrappers with a swap button.
They have Action  but no real Perception, no Memory, and shallow Reasoning.
That's not an agent. That's a chatbot with a wallet.
And in DeFi, that difference costs real money.
The 4 parts aren't optional. They're the architecture.
Miss one your agent is incomplete.
Miss the Action layer controls your agent is dangerous
